<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12214a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12214a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12214a"> 214(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> SP = 5 acts</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">De l&agrave; vient que tant de h&eacute;ros sont des personnages de th&eacute;&acirc;tre, dont l&apos;histoire se d&eacute;compose en situations, l&apos;&ecirc;tre en attitudes et en gestes et dont le caract&egrave;re, que rien d&apos;autre n&apos;a d&ucirc; d&eacute;terminer, se compose, par contre, en caract&egrave;re dramatique. <br><font color="green">[This is why so many heroes are theatrical characters whose history can be divided in episodes, whose being in attitudes and gestures and whose character, which could not be determined by anything else, is determined, on the other hand, by a dramatic character]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LXVII</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
